Reference materials:
	https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/PCI_passthrough_via_OVMF
	https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/libvirt
	https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/QEMU
	https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/KVM

Assumes the following:
	General:
		libvirt and the `qemu-system-x86_64` binary are present on the system
		`/usr/share/edk2-ovmf/x64/OVMF_CODE.fd` contains the OVMF VM firmware
		`/var/lib/libvirt/qemu/nvram/kvm_VARS.fd` contains the generated nvram image for the VM
	Storage:
		The boot device / image to pass through is `/var/lib/libvirt/images/kvm.qcow2`
	Passthrough:
		PCI device 03:00.0 (GPU) is to be passed through and has been hooked by vfio-pci
	Domain details:
		Domain name = 'kvm'
		Pre-generated UUID
	Host config:
		Arch Linux with kernel 5.12.10
		8 logical host CPUs
		Over 8GiB host RAM
		IOMMU, VT-d, EFI enabled
	Guest config:
		i440fx chipset is to be used
			(older than the newer q35 chipset for compatibility reasons)
		Windows 10 x64
	Input:
		`/var/lib/libvirt/inputs/event-<kbd0,kbd1,mouse0>`,
			are all symlinks to their respective input devices in /dev/...
	Network:
		libvirt / virtio networking is properly configured
	Audio:
		PulseAudio is running and routed from the current user to /tmp/pulse-socket
		/tmp/pulse-socket is the default server for PulseAudio running with the root user
		The PulseAudio `cookie` to access user audio is located in
			$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/.config/pulse/cookie for the root user (/root)

Useful programs:
	virt-manager
-->
